title: Miami tabbed 10th in preseason hockey poll
text:
Miami tabbed 10th in preseason hockey poll 
Updated: Mon, Oct 05 2015, 05:31 PM 
OXFORD, Ohio (WKRC) -- Another preseason national poll pegs the Miami hockey team to be in contention for its 10th NCAA Tournament appearance in 11 seasons. 
USA Today/USA Hockey Magazine pegged Miami 10th in its preseason national poll, which was released on Monday. The RedHawks were one of the five teams from the National Collegiate Hockey Conference to see their names in the top-15 poll. Preseason NCHC favorite Minnesota Duluth checked in at No. 3, North Dakota is next at No. 4, Denver sits at No. 5, Miami is ranked 10th while Omaha rounds out the NCHC contingent at No. 11. Additionally, St. Cloud State also received votes in the poll. 
The RedHawks are also ranked in the USCHO.com preseason poll, which came out last week and tabbed them 11th. Boston College is the top ranked team in both polls. 
Miami begins the 2015-16 regular season on Friday against defending national champion and seventh-ranked Providence.
